item.title: CVE-2017-17166|2024-08-05T20:43:59.930Z -- huawei%20technologies%20co.%2C%20ltd. -- dp300%2C%20secospace%20usg6300%2Csecospace%20usg6500%2Csecospace%20usg6600%2Ctp3206%2C%20vp9660
item.description: Huawei DP300 V500R002C00, Secospace USG6300 V500R001C00, V500R001C20, V500R001C30, V500R001C50, Secospace USG6500 V500R001C00, V500R001C20, V500R001C30, V500R001C50, Secospace USG6600 V500R001C00, V500R001C20, V500R001C30, V500R001C50, TP3206 V100R002C00, VP9660 V500R002C00, V500R002C10 have a resource exhaustion vulnerability. The software does not process certain field of H.323 message properly, a remote unauthenticated attacker could send crafted H.323 message to the device, successful exploit could cause certain service unavailable since the stack memory is exhausted.
